Question: Extract text from html file using java: :I am working on a text crawler and I need to extract a certain text from several sites. I have used jsoup html parser:Document doc = Jsoup.connect("http://www.aljazeera.net/programs/behindthenews/2014/11/9/%D8%A3%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A8%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%B1").get();Elements ps = doc.select("p");String s = Jsoup.parse(ps.text()).text();PrintWriter out = new PrintWriter("newFile.txt", "UTF-8");out.write(s);out.close();This algorithm gets me an unwanted text, the wanted text is under this tag <p dir="rtl">And when I change my selection to Elements ps = doc.select("p dir=rtl");, it returns a compilation error.Is there any way to make it just select this wanted tag?
Please using this api: PrintWriter.write.
Answer: <<<api>>>: PrintWriter.write
<<<code>>>: PrintWriter out = new PrintWriter("newFile.txt", "UTF-8");
out.write(s);
out.close();
<<<explanation>>>: This code will write the string s to the file newFile.txt using the UTF-8 encoding.
